---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Monaco Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/monaco/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
  { title: 'Switzerland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/switzerland' },
  { title: 'Italy for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/italy' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'monacoFit', header: 'Monaco Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€500-715/mo', monacoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€585-835/mo', monacoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€450-645/mo', monacoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€480-685/mo', monacoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'CCSS (Monaco)', entryAge: 'All ages', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: '€400-600/mo', monacoFit: 'Required' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'CCSS (Mandatory)', monthly: '€400-600', annual: '€4,800-7,200' },
  { category: 'Private Top-Up (65-69)', monthly: '€450-715', annual: '€5,400-8,580' },
  { category: 'Private Top-Up (70-74)', monthly: '€615-955', annual: '€7,380-11,460' },
  { category: 'Private Top-Up (75-79)', monthly: '€825-1,280', annual: '€9,900-15,360' },
  { category: 'Princess Grace Hospital', monthly: '€150-300/visit', annual: 'As needed' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Monaco 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Monaco. Mediterranean luxury, no income tax, excellent healthcare, and coverage for affluent retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Monaco"
  subheadline="Monaco offers Mediterranean glamour, no income tax, exceptional safety, world-class events, and proximity to French healthcare—the ultimate luxury microstate for wealthy retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/monaco-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Monaco</h2>
  <p>
    Monaco offers the ultimate luxury retirement: no income tax, Mediterranean climate, exceptional safety (more police per capita than anywhere), world-class events (Grand Prix, yacht shows), and easy access to French Riviera healthcare. For ultra-high-net-worth retirees seeking prestige and tax efficiency, Monaco is unmatched.
  </p>

  <p>
    Monaco is just 2 km²—smaller than Central Park. Monte Carlo is the famous district. Fontvieille is quieter. Nice is 20 minutes away with international airport and major hospital (CHU Nice). Population ~40,000 with only ~9,000 Monégasque citizens. Residency is competitive.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Princess Grace Hospital; Nice backup</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> French; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €10,000-25,000+/month; world's most expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean; mild winters; warm summers</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Glamorous; safe; exclusive</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income tax (French citizens excepted)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Monaco Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Monaco has excellent healthcare through Princess Grace Hospital Centre (CHPG)—modern, well-equipped, serving entire principality. Covers most specialties. CCSS (Caisses Sociales de Monaco) is mandatory social security system covering healthcare at ~80% reimbursement. Complex cases can access CHU Nice or prestigious French hospitals.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare quality is excellent but hospital is small. Nice (CHU Nice Pasteur) provides comprehensive backup 20 minutes away. Private insurance supplements CCSS for copays and faster appointments.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">CCSS Is Mandatory</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      All Monaco residents must enroll in CCSS social security. Covers healthcare at ~80%. Private insurance supplements for copays and choice. Monaco residents can access French healthcare system through agreements. Budget for both CCSS and private top-up.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Monaco residency options for wealthy retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Residency Card</h3>
  <p>
    Requires proof of accommodation (ownership or long-term lease), clean criminal record, and significant financial means (typically €500,000+ in bank). No specific income requirement but must demonstrate ability to live without working.
  </p>

  <h3>Financial Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    Monaco is discretionary—wealth and character assessed. Bank reference letters essential. Property purchase or long lease demonstrates commitment. Competition for residency is real.
  </p>

  <h3>Processing</h3>
  <p>
    Apply through Monaco residency services. Background checks thorough. Expect 3-6 months processing. Residency renewal annual initially, then longer periods.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Monaco:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>CCSS:</strong> Mandatory for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>Private:</strong> Required for residency application</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage:</strong> Must cover Monaco and France</li>
    <li><strong>Standard:</strong> Comprehensive coverage expected</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Monaco</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Two-layer approach: CCSS (mandatory) plus premium private insurance. Private should cover France seamlessly for Nice hospital access. Global coverage common for Monaco residents who travel extensively. Quality expectations high—match lifestyle.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Monaco, premium coverage expected:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Monaco</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong European network, France access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), premium service</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> French company, seamless France coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Service levels:</strong> Must match Monaco lifestyle expectations</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare premium coverage for Monaco residency.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Monaco (EUR):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Total Healthcare Budget</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>CCSS + Private:</strong> €900-1,400/month typical</li>
    <li><strong>Relative to Monaco costs:</strong> Minor compared to housing/lifestyle</li>
    <li><strong>No tax savings on premiums:</strong> But no income tax anyway</li>
    <li><strong>Quality expectations:</strong> Premium coverage standard</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Retired Executive, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €15,000/month income. Monte Carlo apartment. Active lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CCSS + Cigna Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€1,000/month. Premium coverage; Princess Grace + Nice access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Ultra-High-Net-Worth, 74</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €30,000+/month. Fontvieille villa. Global traveler.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CCSS + BUPA Global with worldwide coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€1,500/month. Premium service; global access for frequent travel.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Couple, Yacht Owners, Both 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €20,000/month combined. Monaco base. Mediterranean cruising.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> CCSS + AXA Global couple plan.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€2,200/month combined. Mediterranean coverage; France seamless.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How much wealth do I need for Monaco?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Substantial—no official minimum but expect €500,000+ in bank deposits, plus ability to rent (~€5,000+/month minimum) or buy property (€50,000+/m²). Living costs €10,000-25,000/month. Ultra-wealthy destination.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use French hospitals?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Monaco has healthcare agreements with France. CHU Nice is 20 minutes away. CCSS provides some coverage; private insurance ensures seamless access. Many Monaco residents use Nice for specialized care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the tax advantage real?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes for most—no income tax, no capital gains tax, no wealth tax. Exception: French citizens still pay French tax. For non-French high earners, tax savings can be millions. Professional tax advice essential.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Monaco boring for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Depends—glamorous events (Grand Prix, yacht shows, opera). Excellent restaurants. Small so can feel confined. Easy access to Nice, Côte d'Azur, Italy. Active social scene for wealthy. May feel isolating for some.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from premium providers for Monaco coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Monaco residency requirements and CCSS regulations change. Always verify current requirements with Monaco authorities and consult with professional advisors for tax and insurance guidance.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
